<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="224" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,798,1579]" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,486,798,823]" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Description. Measurements.</emphasis>
Male, body length: 
<quantity box="[712,816,799,823]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" unit="mm" value="9.4">9.40 mm</quantity>
; head width: 
<quantity box="[966,1069,799,823]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.27" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" unit="mm" value="2.27">2.27 mm</quantity>
; crown length×width: 0.85× 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.22" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" unit="mm" value="1.22">1.22 mm</quantity>
; eye width: 
<quantity box="[338,443,834,859]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" unit="mm" value="0.64">0.64 mm</quantity>
; clypeus length: 
<quantity box="[636,741,834,859]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.51" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" unit="mm" value="1.51">1.51 mm</quantity>
; pronotum length×width: 0.96× 
<quantity box="[1102,1206,834,859]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.78" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" unit="mm" value="2.78">2.78 mm</quantity>
; mesonotum length: 
<quantity box="[151,247,871,895]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.31" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" unit="mm" value="1.31">1.31mm</quantity>
. female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,798,1579]" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,460,906,931]" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">External morphology.</emphasis>
Color similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[652,786,908,931]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Thagria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incurvata">
<emphasis box="[652,786,908,931]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">T. incurvata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but apical half of forewing with 8–9 ivory patches (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 48" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[156,1402,205,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1433,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 48. Thagria cerna Wang &amp; Zhang, sp. nov. Holotype: 40. habitus, dorsal view; 41. head and thorax, dorsal view; 42. face; 43. habitus, lateral view; 44. pygofer, lateral view; 45. dorsal connective, pygofer and segment X processes, ventral view; 46. style and connective, ventral view; 47. aedeagus and paraphysis, dorsal view; 48. subgential plate, lateral view. Scale bars: 40 – 43 = 1.0 mm; 44 – 48 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/495024/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Figs. 40–43</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,798,1579]" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">
Head broad but narrower than pronotum, anterior margin rounded; crown short, extended slightly beyond eyes, disk foveate; coronal suture extend to anterior margin of head (
<figureCitation box="[870,954,1014,1039]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 48" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[156,1402,205,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1433,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 48. Thagria cerna Wang &amp; Zhang, sp. nov. Holotype: 40. habitus, dorsal view; 41. head and thorax, dorsal view; 42. face; 43. habitus, lateral view; 44. pygofer, lateral view; 45. dorsal connective, pygofer and segment X processes, ventral view; 46. style and connective, ventral view; 47. aedeagus and paraphysis, dorsal view; 48. subgential plate, lateral view. Scale bars: 40 – 43 = 1.0 mm; 44 – 48 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/495024/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
). Face with clypeus broad, lateral margins slightly convergent to base; clypellus short, with base inflated (
<figureCitation box="[857,941,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 48" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[156,1402,205,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1433,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 48. Thagria cerna Wang &amp; Zhang, sp. nov. Holotype: 40. habitus, dorsal view; 41. head and thorax, dorsal view; 42. face; 43. habitus, lateral view; 44. pygofer, lateral view; 45. dorsal connective, pygofer and segment X processes, ventral view; 46. style and connective, ventral view; 47. aedeagus and paraphysis, dorsal view; 48. subgential plate, lateral view. Scale bars: 40 – 43 = 1.0 mm; 44 – 48 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/495024/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
). Crown, pronotum and mesonotum midline ratio about 1:1:1.5. Venation typical for genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,798,1579]" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,377,1122,1147]" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view broad with narrow caudoventral lobe, caudodorsal margin with a pair of processes, with truncated apex (
<figureCitation box="[546,632,1158,1183]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 48" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[156,1402,205,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1433,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 48. Thagria cerna Wang &amp; Zhang, sp. nov. Holotype: 40. habitus, dorsal view; 41. head and thorax, dorsal view; 42. face; 43. habitus, lateral view; 44. pygofer, lateral view; 45. dorsal connective, pygofer and segment X processes, ventral view; 46. style and connective, ventral view; 47. aedeagus and paraphysis, dorsal view; 48. subgential plate, lateral view. Scale bars: 40 – 43 = 1.0 mm; 44 – 48 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/495024/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
). Segment X in lateral view with ventral processes long, broad basally and tapered to apical 1/3 (
<figureCitation box="[457,544,1194,1219]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 48" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[156,1402,205,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1433,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 48. Thagria cerna Wang &amp; Zhang, sp. nov. Holotype: 40. habitus, dorsal view; 41. head and thorax, dorsal view; 42. face; 43. habitus, lateral view; 44. pygofer, lateral view; 45. dorsal connective, pygofer and segment X processes, ventral view; 46. style and connective, ventral view; 47. aedeagus and paraphysis, dorsal view; 48. subgential plate, lateral view. Scale bars: 40 – 43 = 1.0 mm; 44 – 48 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/495024/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
), curved outward in dorsal aspect; dorsal connective arched, without process basally (
<figureCitation box="[246,332,1230,1255]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 48" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[156,1402,205,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1433,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 48. Thagria cerna Wang &amp; Zhang, sp. nov. Holotype: 40. habitus, dorsal view; 41. head and thorax, dorsal view; 42. face; 43. habitus, lateral view; 44. pygofer, lateral view; 45. dorsal connective, pygofer and segment X processes, ventral view; 46. style and connective, ventral view; 47. aedeagus and paraphysis, dorsal view; 48. subgential plate, lateral view. Scale bars: 40 – 43 = 1.0 mm; 44 – 48 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/495024/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus exceeds half of paraphysis; ventral paraphysis triangulate, very broad basally, distally slightly produced and notched apically, with robust digitate basal process ventrally on one side (
<figureCitation box="[1260,1357,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 48" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[156,1402,205,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1433,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 48. Thagria cerna Wang &amp; Zhang, sp. nov. Holotype: 40. habitus, dorsal view; 41. head and thorax, dorsal view; 42. face; 43. habitus, lateral view; 44. pygofer, lateral view; 45. dorsal connective, pygofer and segment X processes, ventral view; 46. style and connective, ventral view; 47. aedeagus and paraphysis, dorsal view; 48. subgential plate, lateral view. Scale bars: 40 – 43 = 1.0 mm; 44 – 48 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/495024/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Figs. 47</figureCitation>
). Style very short. Connective longitudinally rectangular (
<figureCitation box="[752,844,1302,1327]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 48" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[156,1402,205,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1433,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 48. Thagria cerna Wang &amp; Zhang, sp. nov. Holotype: 40. habitus, dorsal view; 41. head and thorax, dorsal view; 42. face; 43. habitus, lateral view; 44. pygofer, lateral view; 45. dorsal connective, pygofer and segment X processes, ventral view; 46. style and connective, ventral view; 47. aedeagus and paraphysis, dorsal view; 48. subgential plate, lateral view. Scale bars: 40 – 43 = 1.0 mm; 44 – 48 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/495024/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate slender, rounded apically, with numerous fine long setae apically (
<figureCitation box="[543,627,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 48" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[156,1402,205,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1433,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 48. Thagria cerna Wang &amp; Zhang, sp. nov. Holotype: 40. habitus, dorsal view; 41. head and thorax, dorsal view; 42. face; 43. habitus, lateral view; 44. pygofer, lateral view; 45. dorsal connective, pygofer and segment X processes, ventral view; 46. style and connective, ventral view; 47. aedeagus and paraphysis, dorsal view; 48. subgential plate, lateral view. Scale bars: 40 – 43 = 1.0 mm; 44 – 48 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/495024/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
